Solved. 

Solved by request `READ_PHONE_STATE` permission. For some reason Mapbox uses READ_PHONE_STATE. I declared in the `AndroidManifest.xml` but requesting permission manually are crucial.

Hence, the solution:


```java
public void requestReadPhoneStatePermission(Activity activity)
{
        if (Build.VERSION.SDK_INT &gt;= Build.VERSION_CODES.R)
        {
            if (ActivityCompat.checkSelfPermission(
                    activity,
                    Manifest.permission.READ_PHONE_STATE
            ) != PackageManager.PERMISSION_GRANTED)
            {
                ActivityCompat.requestPermissions(
                        activity,
                        new String[]{
                                Manifest.permission.READ_PHONE_STATE
                        },
                        0x1
                );
            }
        }
}
```

And called in the `Application.java` onCreate()

```java
this.requestReadPhoneStatePermission(this);
```

